        treatment: "Mild hemophilia A: desmopressin (DDAVP) 0.3mcg/kg IV or intranasal (300mcg for <50kg, 150mcg for <50kg? Actually: <50kg: 150mcg, >50kg: 300mcg) raises factor VIII 3-5 fold. Severe hemophilia A: factor VIII replacement (recombinant or plasma-derived) 25-50 units/kg q12-24h for mild bleed, 50-75 units/kg q8-12h for severe bleed, or continuous infusion. Hemophilia B: factor IX replacement 50-100 units/kg (half-life longer, q24h). Prophylaxis (for severe): factor VIII 25-40 units/kg 3x/week or factor IX 40-60 units/kg 2x/week (prevents hemarthrosis, preserves joints). Treat bleeding: RICE (rest, ice, compression, elevation), avoid NSAIDs (use acetaminophen), avoid IM injections. Gene therapy (hemophilia B, experimental).",
