        ddx: ["ITP (immune thrombocytopenic purpura): isolated thrombocytopenia, normal WBC/Hb, normal PT/PTT, precedes by viral illness, antiplatelet antibodies", "TTP (thrombotic thrombocytopenic purpura): thrombocytopenia, microangiopathic hemolytic anemia (schistocytes), fever, renal failure, neurologic symptoms", "HUS (hemolytic uremic syndrome): thrombocytopenia, microangiopathic hemolytic anemia, renal failure (oliguria, hypertension), preceded by diarrhea (E. coli O157)", "DIC (disseminated intravascular coagulation): thrombocytopenia, prolonged PT/PTT, low fibrinogen, elevated D-dimer, underlying sepsis or malignancy", "Leukemia: thrombocytopenia, anemia, neutropenia, blasts on smear, fever, bone pain, lymphadenopathy, hepatosplenomegaly", "Aplastic anemia: pancytopenia, reticulocytopenia, normal MCV, no blasts, hypocellular bone marrow", "Drug-induced (quinine, sulfa, heparin, valproic acid, carbamazepine)"],
        ix: ["CBC with platelet count (isolated thrombocytopenia suggests ITP; pancytopenia suggests leukemia or aplastic anemia)", "Peripheral smear (confirm low platelets, exclude clumping, look for schistocytes in TTP/HUS, blasts in leukemia)", "PT, PTT, fibrinogen, D-dimer (if DIC suspected)", "BUN, creatinine (renal failure in HUS, TTP)", "LDH, haptoglobin, bilirubin (hemolysis in TTP/HUS)", "Direct Coombs test (if autoimmune hemolysis suspected)", "Bone marrow aspiration (if pancytopenia, abnormal cells, or age >10y, to exclude leukemia, aplastic anemia)"],
