        treatment: "Incision and drainage (I&D) - definitive treatment. Incision over fluctuance (cruciate or linear incision along skin lines), break up loculations with hemostat or finger, irrigate with saline, pack with iodoform gauze (changed daily until healed, 1-2 weeks). Antibiotics: not routinely needed for simple abscess in immunocompetent patients after drainage. Indications for antibiotics: large abscess (>5cm), surrounding cellulitis, fever, immunocompromised, diabetes, prosthetic valve/joint, S. aureus bacteremia risk, failed prior drainage. MRSA coverage: TMP-SMX 160/800mg BID, doxycycline 100mg BID, or clindamycin 300mg QID x5-7 days. MSSA: cephalexin 500mg QID or dicloxacillin 500mg QID.",
