        ix: ["BP monitoring (clinic and home)", "Urine protein (baseline, then weekly after 20 weeks to detect superimposed pre-eclampsia)", "CBC, platelets, LFTs, creatinine, uric acid (baseline)", "Echocardiogram (LVH, diastolic dysfunction)", "Fundoscopy (retinopathy)", "Fetal ultrasound (baseline growth, then q4 weeks after 28 weeks for growth restriction)", "NST/BPP twice weekly after 32 weeks (or earlier if growth restriction or superimposed pre-eclampsia)"],
