        overview: "Severe fetal growth restriction (estimated fetal weight <3rd percentile, or <5th percentile with abnormal Dopplers), associated with high perinatal morbidity and mortality.",
        symptoms: ["Maternal: often asymptomatic", "Decreased fetal movements (if severe placental insufficiency)", "No weight gain or fundal height growth (on prenatal visits)"],
        signs: ["Fundal height lagging >4 weeks (screening, 50% sensitive)", "Estimated fetal weight <3rd percentile on ultrasound (or <5th percentile with abnormal Dopplers)", "Abnormal umbilical artery Doppler (absent or reversed end-diastolic flow, indicates severe placental insufficiency)", "Oligohydramnios (amniotic fluid index <5cm)", "Abnormal MCA Doppler (cerebral vasodilation, brain sparing effect)", "Hypertension (if pre-eclampsia or chronic hypertension)"],
        ddx: ["Constitutional small size (EFW <10th percentile, but normal Dopplers, normal amniotic fluid, normal growth velocity, no maternal comorbidities, no fetal anomalies)", "Gestational age error (early ultrasound confirms dates, serial growth shows normal velocity)", "Fetal anomalies (structural, chromosomal, genetic, ultrasound shows anomalies, abnormal Dopplers variable)", "Congenital infection (CMV, toxoplasmosis, rubella, Zika, ultrasound shows intracranial calcifications, hepatosplenomegaly, microcephaly, maternal serology positive)"],
        ix: ["Serial fetal ultrasound (q2-4 weeks for growth, amniotic fluid, biophysical profile)", "Umbilical artery Doppler (if absent or reversed end-diastolic flow, indicates severe placental insufficiency, increased risk of fetal demise)", "Middle cerebral artery Doppler (if cerebral vasodilation (PI <5th percentile) indicates brain sparing effect)", "Uterine artery Doppler (notching indicates placental insufficiency)", "Biophysical profile (BPP, if <6/10, or <4/10 with abnormal Dopplers, indicates fetal acidemia)", "Non-stress test (NST, if non-reactive or late decelerations, indicates fetal distress)", "Maternal evaluation (BP, urine protein, glucose, autoimmune markers)", "Fetal anatomy survey (exclude anomalies)", "TORCH titers (if suspected congenital infection)"],
        treatment: "Severe IUGR (<3rd percentile, or <5th percentile with abnormal Dopplers): admit to hospital. Daily NST or BPP, umbilical artery Doppler q48h. Corticosteroids (betamethasone 12mg IM q24h x2) for fetal lung maturity if <34 weeks. Magnesium sulfate for neuroprotection if <32 weeks. Antihypertensives if pre-eclampsia. Delivery if: reversed end-diastolic flow (≥34 weeks, or <34 weeks with BPP <6, or recurrent late decelerations, or worsening oligohydramnios), absent end-diastolic flow (≥37 weeks, or <37 weeks with BPP <8, or abnormal MCA Doppler), or persistent non-reactive NST. Mode: C-section if cervix unfavorable or fetal distress. Postnatal: NICU care (hypoglycemia, hypothermia, polycythemia, feeding difficulties).",
        complication: ["Fetal demise (5-10% if severe IUGR with abnormal Dopplers)", "Neonatal: prematurity (50-80%), respiratory distress syndrome, necrotizing enterocolitis, intraventricular hemorrhage, sepsis, hypoglycemia, hypothermia, polycythemia, thrombocytopenia", "Long-term: cerebral palsy (5-10%), cognitive impairment (10-20%), metabolic syndrome, hypertension, diabetes, cardiovascular disease in adulthood"],
        prevention: "Smoking cessation (reduces risk by 50%), optimize pre-pregnancy weight, treat chronic hypertension, diabetes, and autoimmune disease before pregnancy, low-dose aspirin for high-risk women, good nutrition, treat infections, regular prenatal care",
        epidemiology: "10% of pregnancies have EFW <10th percentile, 2-3% have severe IUGR (<3rd percentile). Risk factors: maternal smoking (30%), chronic hypertension (20%), pre-eclampsia (15%), diabetes (10%), autoimmune disease (5%), multiple gestation (25%), congenital infection (5%), fetal anomalies (5%)"
