        ix: ["Ultrasound (may show retroplacental clot (30-50% sensitivity, higher with large abruption), placental separation, fetal heart rate, biophysical profile)", "CBC (hemoglobin drop, thrombocytopenia if DIC)", "Coagulation profile (PT/INR, PTT, fibrinogen, D-dimer) - fibrinogen <200mg/dL indicates DIC", "Kleihauer-Betke test (fetomaternal hemorrhage, if Rh-negative)", "Blood type and crossmatch (4-6 units PRBCs, FFP, platelets)", "Fetal monitoring (NST: late decelerations, bradycardia, absent variability)"],
        treatment: "Immediate delivery (definitive treatment). Severe abruption (maternal shock, fetal distress, coagulopathy, or >20-30% placental separation): emergency C-section (if cervix unfavorable or fetal distress). Mild-moderate abruption (<34 weeks, no fetal distress, stable): expectant management with hospitalization, betamethasone for fetal lung maturity, deliver when stable. Resuscitation: IV fluids (NS or LR 2-3L bolus), blood transfusion (PRBCs, FFP, platelets if DIC), vasopressors (norepinephrine if shock). Treat DIC: cryoprecipitate (fibrinogen), platelets, FFP. Postpartum: monitor for hemorrhage (uterine atony, give oxytocin, methylergonovine, misoprostol, carboprost).",
