        ddx: ["Uterine atony (70-80% of PPH, boggy uterus, responds to massage and uterotonics)", "Genital tract lacerations (40-60% of PPH, atony also present, visible bleeding from laceration, uterus well-contracted)", "Retained placenta (10-20%, incomplete placenta or membranes, bleeding, uterus not well-contracted)", "Uterine inversion (rare, 0.1%, visible fundus, shock, no uterus on bimanual exam)", "Coagulopathy (DIC, 1-2%, from abruption, sepsis, amniotic fluid embolism, bleeding from IV sites, petechiae)"],
        ix: ["Clinical diagnosis (visual estimation of blood loss, weigh pads and drapes, 1g = 1mL)", "CBC (hemoglobin drop, baseline and q4-6h)", "Coagulation profile (PT/INR, PTT, fibrinogen, D-dimer, if suspected DIC)", "Blood type and crossmatch", "Ultrasound (retained products, uterine inversion, free fluid)"],
        treatment: "Medical (uterotonics): oxytocin 10-40 units IV infusion (first-line), methylergonovine 0.2mg IM (if no hypertension), carboprost (15-methyl PGF2α) 0.25mg IM q15min (max 2mg, if no asthma), misoprostol 800-1000mcg PR (if no IV access). Uterine massage (bimanual compression). Mechanical: intrauterine balloon tamponade (Bakri balloon, 500mL saline, effective 80-90%). Uterine packing (obsolete). Surgical: uterine artery ligation (O'Leary technique), B-Lynch suture (compression suture), internal iliac artery ligation, hysterectomy (if all else fails). Treat lacerations (repair with absorbable suture). Treat retained placenta (manual removal under anesthesia, curettage). Treat inversion (manual replacement, tocolytics (terbutaline), then oxytocin). Transfuse PRBCs (if Hb <7, or <8 with ongoing bleeding, or <9 with cardiovascular disease), FFP (if PT/INR >1.5), platelets (if <50,000), cryoprecipitate (if fibrinogen <100).",
