        ddx: ["Acute MI (chest pain, ECG changes, troponin elevated, no pulsatile mass)", "Perforated ulcer (board-like rigidity, free air on CXR, no pulsatile mass)", "Acute pancreatitis (epigastric pain radiating to back, lipase >3x normal, no pulsatile mass)", "Renal colic (flank pain radiating to groin, hematuria, no pulsatile mass)", "Mesenteric ischemia (pain out of proportion, lactate elevated, no pulsatile mass)", "Aortic dissection (tearing chest pain radiating to back, BP differential, widened mediastinum on CXR)"],
        ix: ["Bedside ultrasound (rapid diagnosis, AAA >5.5cm, free fluid in abdomen, sensitivity 100%, specific 99%, first-line)", "CT angiography (if stable, definitive, shows rupture site, extent, anatomy for endovascular repair)", "CBC, coagulation profile, blood type and crossmatch (massive transfusion protocol)", "ECG (exclude MI)", "Chest X-ray (widened mediastinum if dissection)"],
        treatment: "Immediate surgical repair (open or endovascular) - definitive. Resuscitation with permissive hypotension (target SBP 80-90) to prevent further bleeding before clamp. Massive transfusion protocol (PRBCs:FFP:platelets 1:1:1). Type O-negative blood until crossmatch. IV access (2 large bore 16G or central line). Emergency open repair (infrarenal aortic cross-clamp, tube or bifurcated graft) if anatomy unsuitable for EVAR or unstable. Endovascular aneurysm repair (EVAR) if anatomy suitable (neck length >15mm, diameter 18-32mm, angulation <60°) and patient stable. ICU care post-op.",
