        treatment: "ABCs: oxygen (if hypoxic), bag-valve-mask ventilation (if apnea, rare), intubation if persistent respiratory depression or coma. IV fluids (NS or LR 1-2L bolus) if hypotensive. Flumazenil 0.2mg IV over 30 seconds, repeat 0.3mg, then 0.5mg q1min (max 3mg). Response within 1-2min (if no response, consider other cause). Contraindications: chronic benzodiazepine use (risk of seizures), co-ingestion of proconvulsants (TCAs, cocaine, amphetamines), suspected elevated ICP, status epilepticus (can worsen seizures). Monitor for recurrent sedation (flumazenil half-life 30-60min, shorter than most benzodiazepines). Continuous flumazenil infusion (0.1-0.5mg/h) if recurrent. Treat withdrawal seizures (benzodiazepines, paradoxically). Activated charcoal 50g PO/NG (if within 1-2h of ingestion).",
        complication: ["Seizures (10-20% if flumazenil given to chronic users, or if co-ingested proconvulsants)", "Status epilepticus (1-2%, if flumazenil given to chronic users)", "Cardiac arrest (rare, from flumazenil-induced seizures or arrhythmias)", "Aspiration pneumonia (5-10%)", "Death (rare, <1%, usually from co-ingestants or complications)"],
