        specialty: "Emergency Medicine", 
        year: "L6", 
        overview: "Life-threatening digoxin overdose causing cardiac arrhythmias (bradycardia, heart block, VT, VF), nausea, vomiting, and visual disturbances.",
        symptoms: ["Nausea, vomiting, anorexia (most common, 50-70%)", "Fatigue, weakness", "Dizziness, confusion", "Visual disturbances (yellow-green halos (xanthopsia), blurred vision, scotomas, 10-20%)", "Palpitations", "Syncope", "Abdominal pain", "Diarrhea"],
