        ix: ["Serum digoxin level (therapeutic 0.8-2.0 ng/mL, toxic >2.0 ng/mL, severe >4.0 ng/mL, but toxicity can occur at lower levels if hypokalemia, hypomagnesemia, or myocardial ischemia)", "ECG (most important: atrial tachycardia with block (PAT with block, most specific), ventricular bigeminy, ventricular ectopy, bradycardia, heart block, QT shortening, ST depression (reverse tick) in V5-V6, T inversion)", "CBC, electrolytes (K (hyperkalemia, poor prognosis if >5.5), Mg, Ca)", "BUN, creatinine (renal function, digoxin clearance)", "ABG (metabolic acidosis)", "Troponin (if cardiac ischemia)"],
        treatment: "ABCs, IV access, cardiac monitor. Atropine 0.5-1mg IV (for bradycardia, heart block, up to 3mg). Temporary pacing (if refractory bradycardia, heart block). Magnesium sulfate 2g IV (for arrhythmias, even if Mg normal). Lidocaine 1-1.5mg/kg IV (for VT). Phenytoin 15mg/kg IV (for ventricular arrhythmias, not first-line). Digoxin-specific antibody fragments (Fab, Digibind, DigiFab) - definitive treatment. Indications: life-threatening arrhythmias (VT, VF, advanced heart block), potassium >5.5, massive overdose (>10mg), hemodynamic instability, end-organ dysfunction. Dose (number of vials) = (digoxin level x weight in kg) / 100 (or for acute overdose: ingested dose (mg) / 0.5mg per vial). Administer over 30min. Treat hyperkalemia: calcium gluconate 10% 10-20mL IV (if K >6.5, but use cautiously (may worsen digoxin toxicity), insulin + glucose, albuterol, kayexalate, dialysis (if refractory, but digoxin not dialyzable, Fab is treatment)). Avoid calcium if possible (risk of asystole). Avoid cardioversion (risk of VF). Avoid class Ia (procainamide), Ic (flecainide), and class III (amiodarone) antiarrhythmics (worsen toxicity).",
        complication: ["Cardiac arrhythmias (VT, VF, asystole, 30-50%)", "Cardiac arrest (10-20%)", "Hyperkalemia (20-30%, K >5.5, poor prognosis)", "Acute kidney injury (10-20%, from hypotension)", "Death (5-10% with treatment, 20-30% without, higher if K >5.5, elderly, renal failure, delayed Fab)"],
