        treatment: "Massive transfusion protocol (MTP): activate early (SBP <90, HR >120, or lactate >4, or base deficit >6, or hemodynamic instability, or suspected massive bleeding). Ratio: PRBCs:FFP:platelets = 1:1:1 (or 1:1:2). Give 6 units PRBCs, 6 units FFP, 6 units platelets (or 1 apheresis unit). Tranexamic acid (TXA) 1g IV over 10min, then 1g over 8h (if within 3h of injury, CRASH-2 trial, reduces mortality). Calcium replacement: calcium gluconate 10% 10-20mL IV (or calcium chloride 10% 5-10mL IV) after every 4-6 units PRBCs (citrate anticoagulant binds calcium). Resuscitation: permissive hypotension (target SBP 80-90) until bleeding controlled (to prevent clot disruption). IV fluids: NS or LR 500mL-1L bolus, then minimize (avoid hemodilution). Stop bleeding: surgery (laparotomy, thoracotomy, vascular repair), angiography (embolization), pelvic binder, tourniquet (for extremity hemorrhage).",
