        treatment: "High-quality CPR (100-120/min, depth 5-6cm, full chest recoil, minimize interruptions, rotate compressor q2min). Airway: supraglottic airway (SGA) or endotracheal intubation (ETT). Breathing: ventilations 10/min (1 breath q6s), avoid hyperventilation (increases intrathoracic pressure, decreases venous return). IV/IO access. Epinephrine 1mg IV/IO q3-5min. Identify and treat reversible causes (H's and T's): Hypovolemia (IV fluids 1-2L NS/LR, blood transfusion), Hypoxia (100% oxygen, intubation), Hydrogen ion (acidosis) (sodium bicarbonate 1mEq/kg if pH <7.1, or known hyperkalemia, TCA overdose), Hyperkalemia (calcium gluconate 10% 10mL IV, insulin + glucose, albuterol, sodium bicarbonate), Hypoglycemia (D50 50mL IV), Hypothermia (active rewarming). Tension pneumothorax (needle decompression, chest tube), Tamponade (pericardiocentesis), Toxins (specific antidotes (naloxone, flumazenil, sodium bicarbonate, etc.)), Thrombosis (PE: thrombolytics (alteplase 50mg IV, then 50mg over 30min); MI: PCI, thrombolytics).",
