        prevention: "Early recognition and treatment of reversible causes, high-quality CPR, rapid defibrillation for shockable rhythms, post-resuscitation care (targeted temperature management, coronary angiography, hemodynamic support, seizure control)",
        epidemiology: "20-30% of in-hospital cardiac arrests, 30-40% of out-of-hospital cardiac arrests, survival to hospital discharge 10-20% (worse than VF/VT 30-40%), most common causes: hypovolemia (30%), hypoxia (20%), PE (10%), MI (10%), tamponade (5%), tension pneumothorax (5%), hyperkalemia (5%), hypothermia (1-2%)"
