        signs: ["ETCO2 elevation (sudden, unexplained, despite increased minute ventilation)", "Tachycardia (refractory to treatment)", "Hyperthermia (rapid rise, >40°C)", "Muscle rigidity (masseter spasm after succinylcholine, generalized rigidity)", "Hypoxia (from increased O2 consumption)", "Metabolic acidosis (ABG: pH <7.2, base deficit >8)", "Hyperkalemia (K >6.0, from muscle breakdown)", "Hypercalcemia (Ca >5.5)", "Hyperphosphatemia", "Elevated CK (>20,000 U/L, peaks 12-24h)", "Myoglobinuria (dark red-brown urine)", "DIC (if severe, prolonged)"],
        ddx: ["Neuroleptic malignant syndrome (NMS, antipsychotics, gradual onset (days), rigidity, fever, autonomic instability, no anesthesia trigger)", "Serotonin syndrome (SSRIs, MAOIs, hyperthermia, rigidity, myoclonus, hyperreflexia, no anesthesia trigger)", "Sepsis (fever, tachycardia, hypotension, source of infection, no anesthesia trigger)", "Thyroid storm (fever, tachycardia, agitation, goiter, no anesthesia trigger)", "Pheochromocytoma (hypertension, tachycardia, headache, diaphoresis, no anesthesia trigger)"],
        ix: ["ETCO2 (sudden unexplained elevation, earliest sign)", "ABG (metabolic acidosis, hypercarbia, hypoxia)", "CBC, electrolytes (K, Ca, Mg, Phos), glucose", "CK (elevated, >20,000 U/L)", "Creatinine (AKI from rhabdomyolysis)", "Myoglobin (urine, serum, elevated)", "Coagulation profile (DIC)", "Core temperature (rectal or esophageal, rapid rise)"],
        treatment: "Immediately stop triggering agents (volatile anesthetics, succinylcholine). Hyperventilate with 100% oxygen (10-15L/min, minute ventilation 2-3x normal). Dantrolene 2.5mg/kg IV bolus, repeat q5min until response (max 10mg/kg, total up to 30-40mg/kg). Dantrolene inhibits calcium release from sarcoplasmic reticulum. IV fluids: NS or LR 15-30mL/kg bolus, then 150-200mL/h (maintain urine output >2mL/kg/h). Cooling measures: ice packs (axillae, groin, neck), cold IV fluids (NS 10-20mL/kg), gastric lavage with cold saline, bladder lavage, cooling blanket. Stop cooling when temperature <38.5°C (avoid overshoot). Correct hyperkalemia: calcium gluconate 10% 10-20mL IV, insulin + glucose, albuterol. Bicarbonate 1-2 mEq/kg IV (if pH <7.2). Treat arrhythmias: amiodarone 150mg IV (avoid calcium channel blockers (verapamil, diltiazem) with dantrolene (may cause hyperkalemia, cardiovascular collapse)). Monitor for recurrence (dantrolene q6h x24h, then q8h x24h). ICU care.",
