        prevention: "Screen family history (RYR1 mutations, previous MH reactions). Avoid triggering agents in susceptible patients (use total IV anesthesia (propofol, fentanyl, midazolam), nondepolarizing muscle relaxants (rocuronium, vecuronium)). Dantrolene prophylaxis (controversial). MH cart available in all ORs (dantrolene, ice, cooling equipment). Educate anesthesia providers. MH hotline (1-800-644-9737).",
        epidemiology: "1 in 10,000-50,000 anesthetics, more common in children, young adults, male predominance (2:1), autosomal dominant (RYR1 gene, chromosome 19q13, 50% penetrance), mortality 5-10% (down from 80% before dantrolene)"
