        treatment: "Immediately stop antipsychotic (first-line). Supportive care: IV fluids (NS or LR 2-3L bolus, then 150-200mL/h) to maintain urine output >2mL/kg/h. Cooling measures: ice packs, cooling blanket, cold IV fluids, if temperature >39°C. Treat hyperthermia (avoid antipyretics (acetaminophen, NSAIDs) - ineffective, worsen liver injury). Benzodiazepines: lorazepam 1-2mg IV q4-6h (for agitation, catatonia). Dantrolene 2.5mg/kg IV, repeat up to 10mg/kg (for severe rigidity, hyperthermia, may reduce mortality). Bromocriptine (dopamine agonist) 2.5-5mg PO/NG q6-8h (up to 20mg q6h), or amantadine 100-200mg PO BID (if bromocriptine not available). ECT (electroconvulsive therapy) for refractory NMS (catatonia, severe rigidity). Treat rhabdomyolysis (IV fluids, bicarbonate, mannitol). Treat AKI (dialysis if needed). ICU care.",
