        epidemiology: "0.1-0.5% of patients on antipsychotics (higher with high-potency, rapid escalation, IM administration), 10,000-20,000 US cases annually, more common in young adults, male predominance (2:1), risk factors: dehydration, agitation, exhaustion, prior NMS, organic brain disease, MR, Parkinson's, bipolar disorder, mortality 10-20% (down from 30-50% in 1980s)"
