        ix: ["High-resolution CT chest (HRCT, gold standard: IPF: usual interstitial pneumonia (UIP) pattern (honeycombing, traction bronchiectasis, bibasilar, subpleural, peripheral, with or without ground-glass); NSIP (ground-glass, reticular, lower lobe predominant); COP (organizing pneumonia, peripheral, patchy, reverse halo sign); sarcoidosis (bilateral hilar lymphadenopathy, micronodules, upper lobe fibrosis))", "Pulmonary function tests (restrictive pattern: FVC ↓, FEV1/FVC normal or ↑, TLC ↓, DLCO ↓ (gas exchange impairment))", "ABG (hypoxemia, PaO2 ↓, PaCO2 normal or ↓ (early), ↑ in advanced)", "6-minute walk test (desaturation >4% or SpO2 <88% indicates significant impairment, predicts mortality)", "CBC, ESR, CRP (elevated in inflammatory ILD)", "Autoantibodies (ANA, RF, anti-CCP, anti-Scl-70, anti-Jo-1, anti-Ro, anti-La, ANCA) for connective tissue disease", "ACE (elevated in sarcoidosis)", "Bronchoscopy with BAL (lymphocytosis in sarcoidosis, hypersensitivity pneumonitis; neutrophilia in IPF)", "Lung biopsy (surgical or transbronchial, if HRCT not diagnostic)"],
