        overview: "Mean pulmonary artery pressure (mPAP) >20 mmHg at rest, classified into 5 groups (pulmonary arterial hypertension (PAH), left heart disease, lung disease/hypoxia, chronic thromboembolic, multifactorial).",
        symptoms: ["Dyspnea on exertion (most common, early)", "Fatigue", "Chest pain (angina, from RV ischemia)", "Syncope (exertional, from low cardiac output)", "Palpitations (atrial arrhythmias)", "Hemoptysis (from bronchial artery collaterals)", "Hoarseness (Ortner syndrome, from enlarged pulmonary artery compressing recurrent laryngeal nerve)"],
        signs: ["Accentuated P2 (loud pulmonic component of S2, palpable)", "Right ventricular heave (parasternal lift, from RV hypertrophy)", "S3 gallop (right ventricular, at LLSB)", "S4 gallop (right atrial, from increased preload)", "Pansystolic murmur of tricuspid regurgitation (at LLSB, increases with inspiration)", "Diastolic murmur of pulmonic regurgitation (Graham Steell murmur, at LUSB)", "JVD (elevated JVP, prominent a wave or v wave)", "Peripheral edema (from right heart failure)", "Hepatomegaly, ascites (from right heart failure)", "Cyanosis (if right-to-left shunt through PFO)", "Clubbing (if associated with congenital heart disease or liver disease)"],
        ddx: ["Group 1: Pulmonary arterial hypertension (PAH): idiopathic, heritable, drug-induced (appetite suppressants, dasatinib, methamphetamine), connective tissue disease (scleroderma, SLE), congenital heart disease (Eisenmenger), portal hypertension, HIV, schistosomiasis", "Group 2: Left heart disease: left ventricular systolic or diastolic dysfunction, valvular heart disease (mitral stenosis, regurgitation, aortic stenosis)", "Group 3: Lung disease/hypoxia: COPD, interstitial lung disease, sleep-disordered breathing, high altitude", "Group 4: Chronic thromboembolic pulmonary hypertension (CTEPH): from recurrent or unresolved pulmonary emboli", "Group 5: Multifactorial: sarcoidosis, histiocytosis, neurofibromatosis, Takayasu, renal failure, thyroid disorders"],
        ix: ["Echocardiogram (estimated RVSP = 4 x (TR velocity)^2 + RAP, if >35-40 mmHg suggests PH, RV dilation, hypertrophy, flattening of interventricular septum, right atrial enlargement, pericardial effusion)", "Right heart catheterization (gold standard: mPAP >20 mmHg, PCWP ≤15 (pre-capillary PH, groups 1,3,4,5) or >15 (post-capillary PH, group 2))", "Pulmonary function tests (rule out lung disease, group 3)", "V/Q scan (rule out CTEPH, group 4, segmental or subsegmental mismatched defects)", "CT pulmonary angiography (CTEPH: chronic clots, webs, bands, right ventricular enlargement)", "CBC, ANA, RF, anti-Scl-70 (connective tissue disease), HIV, LFTs (portal hypertension)", "6-minute walk test (distance, desaturation, predicts prognosis)", "BNP or NT-proBNP (elevated, correlates with severity, prognosis)"],
        treatment: "Supportive: oxygen (if SpO2 <90%), diuretics (furosemide 20-80mg daily) for right heart failure, digoxin 0.125-0.25mg daily (if atrial arrhythmias, RV failure), warfarin (INR 2-3) for IPH, CTEPH, or Eisenmenger (controversial). PAH-specific therapy (group 1): calcium channel blockers (nifedipine 30-240mg daily, diltiazem 120-720mg daily) if vasoreactive (10% of IPAH). Endothelin receptor antagonists: bosentan 62.5-125mg BID, ambrisentan 5-10mg daily, macitentan 10mg daily. Phosphodiesterase-5 inhibitors: sildenafil 20-40mg TID, tadalafil 40mg daily. Prostacyclin analogues: epoprostenol (IV), treprostinil (IV, SC, inhaled, oral), iloprost (inhaled). Guanylate cyclase stimulator: riociguat 0.5-2.5mg TID (for PAH, CTEPH). CTEPH (group 4): pulmonary endarterectomy (surgical, curative), riociguat if inoperable. Lung transplantation (if refractory, age <65).",
        complication: ["Right heart failure (50-80% of advanced PH, most common cause of death)", "Syncope (20-30%)", "Atrial arrhythmias (atrial fibrillation, flutter, 20-30%)", "Ventricular arrhythmias (VT, VF, 5-10%)", "Sudden cardiac death (5-10%)", "Hemoptysis (5-10%, from bronchial artery collaterals, may be massive, fatal)", "Pregnancy (high risk, 30-50% mortality, contraindicated, termination recommended)", "Death (3-year survival: IPAH 50-70% without treatment, 70-80% with modern therapy, worse for scleroderma-associated PAH 40-50%)"],
        prevention: "Early diagnosis and treatment of underlying cause (left heart disease, lung disease, CTEPH), avoid drugs that cause PAH (appetite suppressants, dasatinib, methamphetamine), treat connective tissue disease, HIV, portal hypertension, congenital heart disease, screening echocardiogram for high-risk patients (scleroderma, family history, congenital heart disease, portal hypertension), treat sleep apnea, oxygen for chronic hypoxemia",
        epidemiology: "mPAP >20 mmHg in 1-2% of adults, 1% of world population (50-100 million), PAH (group 1): 10-50 per million, IPAH 5-10 per million, female predominance (2-4:1), peak 30-50 years, CTEPH (group 4): 1-5% after acute PE, 5-10 per million, 3-year survival 50-70% without treatment, 70-80% with modern therapy"
