        symptoms: ["Cough (new or change in chronic cough, 50-75%)", "Hemoptysis (blood-streaked sputum, 20-50%)", "Dyspnea (from airway obstruction, pleural effusion, or lymphangitic spread)", "Chest pain (dull, persistent, from chest wall invasion or pleural involvement)", "Hoarseness (recurrent laryngeal nerve invasion, from left upper lobe tumors)", "Dysphagia (esophageal invasion)", "Horner syndrome (ptosis, miosis, anhidrosis, from Pancoast tumor (superior sulcus) invading sympathetic chain)", "Pancoast syndrome (shoulder pain radiating to ulnar distribution of arm, hand weakness, from brachial plexus invasion)", "Superior vena cava syndrome (facial swelling, JVD, arm edema, from SVC obstruction)", "Weight loss, fatigue, anorexia (systemic symptoms)", "Paraneoplastic syndromes: hypercalcemia (squamous cell, from PTHrP), SIADH (hyponatremia, small cell), Cushing (ACTH, small cell), Lambert-Eaton (proximal muscle weakness, small cell), clubbing, hypertrophic osteoarthropathy (adenocarcinoma)"],
