        symptoms: ["Severe pain (out of proportion to physical findings, earliest symptom)", "Swelling, erythema (spreading rapidly over hours)", "Bullae (blisters, clear or hemorrhagic)", "Skin necrosis (black, gangrenous areas)", "Fever, chills", "Malaise, altered mental status", "Tachycardia, hypotension (septic shock)"],
        signs: ["Severe tenderness (beyond visible erythema)", "Erythema (rapidly spreading, >1cm/hour)", "Crepitus (subcutaneous gas, 30-40%)", "Bullae (clear, then hemorrhagic)", "Skin necrosis (gray, black, non-viable)", "Anesthesia (skin numbness from nerve destruction)", "Systemic toxicity (fever, tachycardia, hypotension, altered mental status)", "LRINEC score ≥6 high risk"],
        ddx: ["Cellulitis (pain proportional to exam, no systemic toxicity, no crepitus, no bullae, responds to antibiotics)", "Abscess (localized fluctuance, no rapid spread, no systemic toxicity)", "Gas gangrene (Clostridial myonecrosis, muscle involvement, gas in muscle, history of trauma or surgery)", "Fournier gangrene (necrotizing fasciitis of perineum, scrotum, penis, perianal)", "Pyomyositis (muscle abscess, localized, no fascial involvement)"],
        ix: ["Clinical diagnosis (do NOT delay imaging for high suspicion)", "CBC (leukocytosis or leukopenia), CRP (markedly elevated)", "Lactate (elevated >2)", "Creatinine, electrolytes, glucose", "Blood cultures (before antibiotics)", "Wound culture (deep tissue, at surgery)", "CT or MRI (if diagnosis uncertain, shows fascial thickening, gas, fluid, but do NOT delay surgery)", "X-ray (may show subcutaneous gas, low sensitivity)"],
        treatment: "Emergency surgical debridement (within 6 hours of diagnosis) - definitive treatment. Wide debridement of all non-viable tissue, fascia, muscle, skin, until healthy bleeding tissue. Repeat debridement q24-48h until no further necrosis. IV antibiotics: vancomycin 15mg/kg + piperacillin-tazobactam 4.5g q6h + clindamycin 900mg q8h (toxin suppression) + IVIG 2g/kg (for toxic shock). ICU care, vasopressors (norepinephrine), IV fluids, organ support. Hyperbaric oxygen (adjunct, controversial). Reconstructive surgery (skin grafts, flaps) after infection controlled.",
