        signs: ["Localized bone tenderness (over affected bone)", "Swelling (over bone)", "Warmth", "Erythema", "Limited range of motion of adjacent joint (if metaphyseal, adjacent joint reactive effusion)", "Fever (>38.5°C)", "Tachycardia", "Signs of sepsis (if severe)"],
        ddx: ["Septic arthritis (joint pain, swelling, warmth, limited ROM, joint effusion, aspirate shows WBC >50,000, organisms, no bone tenderness unless osteomyelitis extends to joint)", "Cellulitis (skin erythema, warmth, tenderness, but no deep bone tenderness, no fever unless severe, no bone changes on MRI)", "Deep vein thrombosis (leg swelling, pain, Homan sign, no fever, no bone tenderness, ultrasound positive)", "Ewing sarcoma (bone pain, swelling, fever, night pain, weight loss, X-ray shows lytic lesion with onion-skin periosteal reaction, biopsy)", "Osteoid osteoma (night pain, relieved by NSAIDs, X-ray shows lucent nidus with surrounding sclerosis)"],
        ix: ["X-ray (normal for first 7-14 days, then periosteal reaction, lytic lesion, sequestrum (dead bone), involucrum (new bone), late changes)", "MRI (gold standard, shows bone edema (low T1, high STIR), intraosseous abscess, soft tissue abscess, sinus tract, sensitivity 90-100%, specificity 80-90%)", "Bone scan (Tc-99m MDP, increased uptake, sensitive but not specific, 90% sensitive, 70% specific)", "CBC (leukocytosis, left shift, 50-80%)", "CRP (elevated, >100 mg/L, 90-100% sensitive, normalizes with treatment)", "ESR (elevated, >50 mm/h, normalizes slowly)", "Blood cultures (50-80% positive, same organism as bone)", "Bone biopsy (percutaneous CT-guided or open, gold standard: culture, histology (neutrophils, necrosis))"],
        treatment: "IV antibiotics (empiric, before culture results): vancomycin 15mg/kg q12h + ceftriaxone 2g daily (or cefepime 2g q8h) for MRSA + Gram-negative coverage. After culture results: MSSA (nafcillin 2g q4h, or cefazolin 2g q8h), MRSA (vancomycin, daptomycin 6mg/kg daily, linezolid 600mg q12h), Streptococcus (penicillin G 4 million units q4h, or ceftriaxone 2g daily), Gram-negative (ceftriaxone, cefepime, ciprofloxacin). Duration: 4-6 weeks IV, then 2-4 weeks oral if improvement, total 6-8 weeks. Surgical debridement if abscess, sequestrum, or no clinical improvement after 48-72h of antibiotics. Immobilize limb initially, then early ROM after pain controlled. Treat underlying risk factors.",
        complication: ["Chronic osteomyelitis (10-20%, from delayed treatment, sequestrum, biofilm, requires surgical debridement, long-term antibiotics)", "Septic arthritis (10-20%, from extension through growth plate in children, or through bone in adults)", "Pathologic fracture (5-10%, from bone weakening, treat with immobilization, surgery)", "Growth arrest (children, 5-10%, from physeal involvement, leg length discrepancy, angular deformity)", "Abscess formation (intraosseous, subperiosteal, soft tissue, 10-20%, requires drainage)", "Sepsis (5-10%)", "Death (1-2%, from sepsis, in elderly, immunocompromised, delayed treatment)"],
