        signs: ["Synovitis (swollen, tender MCP, PIP, wrists, MTP, knees, elbows, shoulders)", "Loss of range of motion (flexion contractures)", "Deformities: ulnar deviation, swan-neck (PIP hyperextension, DIP flexion), boutonniere (PIP flexion, DIP hyperextension), hitchhiker thumb (MCP flexion, IP hyperextension), hammer toes, claw toes", "Rheumatoid nodules (subcutaneous, on extensor surfaces (elbows, forearms), painless, mobile)", "Vasculitis (digital infarcts, purpura, mononeuritis multiplex (foot drop, wrist drop))", "Pulmonary: crackles (ILD), pleural friction rub", "Cardiac: pericardial friction rub, murmur (valvular)", "Ocular: scleritis (red, painful, deep), episcleritis (red, painless)"],
        ddx: ["Osteoarthritis (no synovitis, no morning stiffness >30 min, no systemic symptoms, X-ray shows joint space narrowing, osteophytes, no erosions, RF/anti-CCP negative)", "Psoriatic arthritis (asymmetric, DIP joints, enthesitis (Achilles, plantar fascia), dactylitis (sausage digit), psoriasis, nail changes (pitting, onycholysis), RF negative, anti-CCP negative)", "Gout (acute monoarticular, severe pain, erythema, tophi, joint aspirate shows urate crystals, elevated uric acid)", "Pseudogout (acute monoarticular, calcium pyrophosphate crystals on aspirate, chondrocalcinosis on X-ray)", "Systemic lupus erythematosus (SLE, malar rash, photosensitivity, oral ulcers, alopecia, serositis, nephritis, ANA positive, anti-dsDNA positive, RF positive but anti-CCP negative)"],
        ix: ["Rheumatoid factor (RF, IgM anti-IgG, 70-80% positive, sensitivity 70%, specificity 80%)", "Anti-CCP (anti-cyclic citrullinated peptide, 80-90% positive, sensitivity 80%, specificity 95-98%, more specific than RF)", "ESR, CRP (elevated, correlate with disease activity)", "CBC (anemia of chronic disease, thrombocytosis, neutropenia in Felty syndrome)", "CMP (normal, unless amyloidosis or drug-induced (methotrexate hepatotoxicity, NSAID nephrotoxicity))", "X-ray (hands, wrists, feet: periarticular osteopenia, soft tissue swelling, joint space narrowing, marginal erosions (bare areas), subluxation, ankylosis)", "MRI (synovitis, tenosynovitis, bone edema, erosions, earlier than X-ray)", "Ultrasound (synovitis, tenosynovitis, power Doppler (active inflammation))", "Chest X-ray (interstitial lung disease, nodules, pleural effusion)", "Rheumatoid nodules biopsy (palisading granuloma, central fibrinoid necrosis)"],
        treatment: "DMARDs (disease-modifying antirheumatic drugs): methotrexate 10-25mg PO/SC weekly (first-line, anchor drug), leflunomide 10-20mg daily, sulfasalazine 1-1.5g BID, hydroxychloroquine 200-400mg daily (mild). Biologic DMARDs (if methotrexate failure after 3-6 months): TNF inhibitors (etanercept 50mg SC weekly, adalimumab 40mg SC q2w, infliximab 3-5mg/kg IV at 0,2,6 weeks then q8w, certolizumab 400mg SC at 0,2,4 weeks then 200mg q2w, golimumab 50mg SC monthly), IL-6 inhibitors (tocilizumab 162mg SC weekly or 8mg/kg IV monthly), anti-CD20 (rituximab 1000mg IV at 0,2 weeks then q6-12 months), T-cell co-stimulation inhibitor (abatacept 125mg SC weekly or 10mg/kg IV monthly), JAK inhibitors (tofacitinib 5mg BID, baricitinib 2-4mg daily, upadacitinib 15mg daily). Glucocorticoids (prednisone 5-20mg daily, or methylprednisolone 40-80mg IM monthly) for bridging until DMARDs effective, or for flares. NSAIDs (ibuprofen, naproxen, celecoxib) for symptomatic relief. Physical therapy, occupational therapy (splints, adaptive devices). Surgery: synovectomy, tendon repair, joint arthroplasty (hip, knee, shoulder, elbow, wrist, MCP), cervical spine fusion (if C1-C2 instability).",
        complication: ["Joint erosions (irreversible, within first 2 years, leading to deformity, disability)", "Extra-articular: rheumatoid nodules (20-30%), Sjogren syndrome (10-20%), vasculitis (1-5%, poor prognosis), interstitial lung disease (10-20%, UIP, NSIP, bronchiolitis, mortality), pleuritis (5-10%), pericarditis (5-10%), scleritis (1-5%, blindness if untreated), Felty syndrome (1%, splenomegaly, neutropenia, recurrent infections), amyloidosis (1%, nephrotic syndrome, renal failure)", "Infections (from immunosuppression, 2-3x risk, especially pneumonia, sepsis, tuberculosis, fungal, opportunistic)", "Lymphoma (2-3x risk, especially with high disease activity, immunosuppression (TNF inhibitors, methotrexate))", "Cardiovascular disease (2-3x risk, from chronic inflammation, MI, stroke, heart failure)", "Osteoporosis (from inflammation, glucocorticoids, immobility)", "Death (5-10 year mortality 30-40%, from cardiovascular disease, infections, amyloidosis, ILD)"],
        prevention: "No prevention, early diagnosis and treatment (treat-to-target, remission or low disease activity within 3-6 months), treat cardiovascular risk factors (statins, aspirin, BP control), screen for latent TB before biologics, vaccines (influenza, pneumococcal, herpes zoster, HPV, hepatitis B), smoking cessation, treat osteoporosis (calcium, vitamin D, bisphosphonates if glucocorticoids), monitor for infections, malignancies, cardiovascular disease",
        epidemiology: "1% of world population (1.5 million US adults), female predominance (3:1), peak 30-50 years, 70-80% RF positive, 80-90% anti-CCP positive, 50-70% have erosions within 2 years without DMARDs, 10-20% have severe disease (erosions, deformities, extra-articular), 5-10 year mortality 30-40%"
