        signs: ["Uterine enlargement (symmetric, globular, 2-3x normal size, tender, 'boggy' (soft, spongy))", "Tenderness (diffuse, worse premenstrually, during menses)", "Anemia (pallor, tachycardia, from menorrhagia)"],
        ddx: ["Uterine fibroids (irregular enlargement, discrete nodules, not tender, no dysmenorrhea, ultrasound shows hypoechoic masses, normal myometrium)", "Endometriosis (nodularity, tenderness, fixed uterus, uterosacral ligament nodules, ovarian endometriomas, dysmenorrhea, dyspareunia, infertility)", "Adenomyoma (focal adenomyosis, pseudonodule, similar to fibroid, MRI shows ill-defined, not encapsulated)", "Leiomyosarcoma (rapid growth, postmenopausal, pain, bleeding, ultrasound shows heterogeneous mass, necrosis, biopsy)"],
        ix: ["Ultrasound (TVUS: myometrial cysts (anechoic lacunae), myometrial heterogeneity, linear striations ('Venetian blind' sign), asymmetrical thickening of myometrium, junctional zone thickness >8mm)", "MRI (gold standard: junctional zone thickening >12mm, or ratio >40%, myometrial cysts, high T2 signal, ill-defined, no capsule, distinguishes from fibroid)", "Saline infusion sonography (SIS, excludes submucosal fibroids, polyps)", "CBC (iron deficiency anemia)", "CA-125 (elevated, but non-specific, 30-50%, from endometriosis, adenomyosis, inflammation)"],
        treatment: "Medical (first-line, for symptomatic relief, preserves fertility): NSAIDs (ibuprofen 400-800mg TID, for dysmenorrhea, menorrhagia), tranexamic acid 1.3g TID x5 days (for menorrhagia), OCPs (oral contraceptives, continuous or cyclic, for dysmenorrhea, menorrhagia), LNG-IUS (levonorgestrel IUD, Mirena, for menorrhagia, dysmenorrhea, reduces bleeding by 90%, pain by 70%), GnRH agonists (leuprolide 3.75mg IM monthly, or elagolix 300mg BID, for 3-6 months, reduces uterine size, symptoms, but side effects (hot flashes, bone loss)), dienogest 2mg daily (progestin, for endometriosis, adenomyosis, dysmenorrhea, pain). Surgical (for severe symptoms, no desire for pregnancy, or failed medical therapy): uterine artery embolization (UAE, for adenomyosis, reduces uterine size by 30-50%, improves symptoms 80-90%, but recurrence 10-20% in 5 years, not for focal adenomyosis). Hysterectomy (definitive, for severe symptoms, no desire for pregnancy, fails medical, UAE). Adenomyomectomy (focal adenomyosis, preserves fertility, laparoscopic, open, recurrence 10-20%).",
